---

## 1. Purpose

The NMPA Product Registration & Compliance System (PRCS) manages the submission, review, approval, and monitoring of pharmaceutical and medical device applications.

The system supports manufacturers, reviewers, compliance officers, and administrators throughout the product lifecycle.

---

## 2. Scope

### In Scope
- New product registration  
- Clinical trial application  
- Technical document submission  
- Regulatory review  
- Approval and rejection workflows  
- Post-market surveillance  
- Compliance reporting  

### Out of Scope
- Financial billing  
- International regulatory submissions  

---

## 3. User Roles

| Role              | Description                              |
|-------------------|------------------------------------------|
| Applicant         | Submits applications and documents       |
| Reviewer          | Reviews and evaluates submissions        |
| Compliance Officer| Handles post-market monitoring           |
| Admin             | Manages system configuration             |

---

